05:57.497 --> 05:58.632
Beer?

05:58.766 --> 06:00.667
Can I have
a beer please?

06:00.800 --> 06:02.134
Thank you.

06:02.269 --> 06:04.905
You know I don't think
he knows it yet, though.

06:05.038 --> 06:06.906
That we broke up.

06:07.040 --> 06:09.975
We just kind of entered
the sexual-tension-in-the-band

06:10.110 --> 06:12.846
part of the
rock 'n' roll cliché.

06:12.978 --> 06:15.581
I could help with the lead-
singer-becomes-a-star

06:15.714 --> 06:17.983
while-her-boyfriend-spends-his
time-in-rehab-teaching-fellow

06:18.117 --> 06:20.887
juicers-Voodoo-Child-on-a
second-hand-Strat...

06:21.721 --> 06:23.089
part of the cliché.

06:24.458 --> 06:26.393
Well, do you think
we're any good?

06:26.526 --> 06:31.197
I think your band can't decide
if it's Guns N' Roses or Hole.

06:31.331 --> 06:33.834
Whatever it is you're all
trying to be, but never will be.

06:33.966 --> 06:35.467
You aren't very nice.

06:36.136 --> 06:38.271
I'm not paid to be nice.

06:38.404 --> 06:41.941
Well, I'm not very nice either,
but I don't get paid for it.

06:42.074 --> 06:46.712
Part of the
not-getting-paid-at-all cliché.

06:46.846 --> 06:48.581
I can help you with that too.

06:48.716 --> 06:50.850
Hey...

06:51.851 --> 06:53.553
Call me.

07:04.497 --> 07:05.932
There you go.

07:07.535 --> 07:08.802
Josh.

07:22.516 --> 07:23.818
Steph!

07:25.386 --> 07:27.822
Oh, you look
really good today.

07:39.132 --> 07:41.701
You think I like doing this?

07:41.834 --> 07:45.238
Don't you think I'd rather be on
the floor watching the Lakers?

07:45.372 --> 07:47.407
What's happening
with, uh, Micky Adams?

07:47.540 --> 07:48.575
I-In terms of...

07:48.709 --> 07:51.744
I-In terms of dropping him,
you fucking moron.

07:51.877 --> 07:54.213
Cobain may be gone,
but somebody's got to keep Courtney

07:54.348 --> 07:55.848
in smack
and ripped stockings.

07:55.983 --> 07:57.350
Well...

07:57.483 --> 07:59.719
And yet again, I'm forced
to deal with the specter

07:59.853 --> 08:01.187
of Micky Adams.

08:01.321 --> 08:03.190
Has Micky
Adams crossed him?

08:03.322 --> 08:06.392
Micky Adams was my friend.
I managed Micky Adams.

08:06.526 --> 08:08.294
I got him high,
and I got him laid,

08:08.427 --> 08:10.430
and I watched him get a quarter
million a year in perpetuity.

08:10.564 --> 08:15.435
And now Micky Adams haunts me
because no one seems to know

08:15.567 --> 08:17.204
how to get rid of him.

08:17.336 --> 08:20.339
Well, we've tried.
He has no agent.

08:20.473 --> 08:21.408
He has no lawyer.

08:21.541 --> 08:24.343
Does he have an address?

08:24.476 --> 08:25.945
Yes.

08:26.980 --> 08:30.918
Then why don't you go there
and drop him?

08:31.050 --> 08:33.019
We've tried.
We've sent people.

08:33.153 --> 08:34.486
- And?
- Well, no one...

08:36.956 --> 08:38.625
No one comes back.

08:41.594 --> 08:43.030
I'll do it.

08:43.163 --> 08:45.599
- Who are you?
- I'm Charlie.

08:45.731 --> 08:47.933
- He works in the mail room.
- Yeah, he's nobody.

08:48.067 --> 08:50.235
Is that what you are,
Charlie?

08:50.370 --> 08:51.404
Nobody?

08:52.739 --> 08:54.408
Nobody's fool.

09:01.880 --> 09:04.117
Why don't you two go?

09:07.553 --> 09:09.288
How long have you been
in the mail room?

09:09.422 --> 09:10.957
Long enough
to know better.

09:11.091 --> 09:12.125
Want my job?
You can have it.

09:12.258 --> 09:14.694
Get your shit
outta here by lunch.

09:14.827 --> 09:16.496
This fucking business,

09:16.629 --> 09:18.097
I feel like
I'm riding a dinosaur

09:18.230 --> 09:20.000
into the jaws
of the apocalypse.

09:20.134 --> 09:22.335
Come here. I want you
to hear something.

09:22.469 --> 09:24.270
This is Micky Adam's
latest offering.

09:24.403 --> 09:26.773
It's a CD he calls, "Doors."

09:26.907 --> 09:29.242
Some kind of homage
to Jim Morrison.

09:30.374 --> 09:31.944
No, it's a very real
homage to masturbation.

09:32.077 --> 09:35.581
- Listen. First track.
- Homage.

09:38.150 --> 09:39.519
Second track.

09:43.023 --> 09:44.091
Third track.

09:44.224 --> 09:45.892
This is my personal
favorite here.

09:48.595 --> 09:50.096
What is that?

09:50.230 --> 09:52.699
It's a coffin.
Unfortunately, it's not his.

09:52.832 --> 09:55.334
If it were, he'd sell more
than two CD's in a decade.

09:55.467 --> 10:00.640
And finally, ten minutes of a
refrigerator opening and closing.

10:02.642 --> 10:03.677
Boy, is he nuts.

10:03.811 --> 10:05.378
Yeah, he's a big crazy baby.

10:05.511 --> 10:08.581
Uploaded leftover from
a drug-addled, pampered,

10:08.716 --> 10:10.650
completely out of control
time in music.

10:10.783 --> 10:12.052
Stephanie!

10:12.184 --> 10:15.521
The bill for which
has somehow landed on my desk.

10:15.654 --> 10:18.692
Go out to Montecito.
Get that big baby to countersign

10:18.825 --> 10:22.495
that buyout agreement that releases
us from blah blah blah blah...

10:22.629 --> 10:23.964
and then maybe...

10:24.096 --> 10:26.399
maybe your mail room days
are over, Charlie.

10:26.933 --> 10:28.168
You got it.

10:29.635 --> 10:31.404
That's the last
great thing he did.

10:31.538 --> 10:33.307
Give it a listen
on the way up to Montecito.

10:33.440 --> 10:35.975
Maybe there's a clue in there on
how to dump his oatmeal-y ass.

10:36.109 --> 10:37.344
How soon do you want this done?

10:37.476 --> 10:39.645
- Yesterday.
- I'm already there.

10:47.153 --> 10:49.990
<i>♪ Come on now, Mr. Sailor Man ♪</i>

10:50.123 --> 10:53.826
<i>♪ Get me off of this key chain
