12:40.133 --> 12:44.871
<i>♪ Little do they know ♪</i>

12:45.605 --> 12:49.276
<i>♪ Little do they know ♪</i>

12:53.178 --> 12:55.447
<i>♪ Shout it from the rooftops ♪</i>

12:55.581 --> 12:58.717
<i>♪ Cause we don't
Really give a damn ♪</i>

13:36.255 --> 13:38.257
That old man is out
of his fucking skull!

13:42.028 --> 13:45.932
I'm Charlie Porter. Um, hello?

14:23.336 --> 14:24.736
Jesus Christ!

14:37.951 --> 14:39.085
Hey!

14:39.219 --> 14:40.721
Fuck!

14:44.155 --> 14:45.658
Who the hell are you?

14:46.525 --> 14:48.227
I'm Charlie.

14:48.361 --> 14:51.329
- Are you one of them?
- What are you doing?

14:51.464 --> 14:53.767
You could have
electrocuted yourself.

14:53.899 --> 14:56.502
You A&R piece of shit.

14:56.635 --> 14:58.437
Do you have any idea how
hard it is to stay under?

14:58.572 --> 15:00.273
How much willpower it takes?

15:00.405 --> 15:04.109
I was recording,
you dipshit!

15:04.243 --> 15:05.979
What the hell do you want?

15:06.113 --> 15:08.248
I'm from Indigo Records.

15:08.381 --> 15:10.983
You actually sound proud
of that, Sparky.

15:11.116 --> 15:13.552
Okay, Mr. Adams, we have
some business to discuss.

15:13.686 --> 15:16.589
I'm an artist.
I don't discuss business.

15:16.722 --> 15:18.524
With all due respect,
I don't think I would call

15:18.658 --> 15:21.327
the sound of doors
opening and closing art.

15:32.839 --> 15:34.641
I'll tell you something, Sparky.

15:35.542 --> 15:37.777
There's nothing more evocative

15:37.909 --> 15:41.581
than the sound of doors
opening and closing.

15:41.714 --> 15:44.217
Nothing more hopeful
and nothing more final.

15:44.350 --> 15:49.254
When you reach my age, if your callowness
and stupidity hasn't already done you in,

15:49.389 --> 15:51.625
which is something
devoutly to be wished...

15:52.725 --> 15:54.528
maybe you'll understand that.

15:56.562 --> 15:57.798
I doubt it.

15:59.164 --> 16:00.433
Hungry?

16:04.537 --> 16:06.739
What is this?

16:06.871 --> 16:10.209
It's a spaghetti and
mayonnaise sandwich. My fave.

16:10.344 --> 16:12.646
Lowell George
turned me on to 'em.

16:12.778 --> 16:14.147
Eat.

16:24.923 --> 16:25.958
Hmm.

16:29.995 --> 16:33.699
Mmm. Is this Sprite?

16:33.833 --> 16:35.434
I haven't had Sprite
in a long time.

16:35.567 --> 16:38.004
Sure, it could be.
Sprite, yeah.

16:38.136 --> 16:41.039
The new Spritelier Sprite.

16:41.173 --> 16:42.408
Ha ha.

16:43.909 --> 16:46.480
You want to know why you don't
have any hair on your ankles?

16:46.613 --> 16:48.648
I didn't know
I don't have hair on my ankles.

16:48.780 --> 16:50.248
How did you know that?

16:51.049 --> 16:55.322
I'm an artist.
I notice everything.

16:55.455 --> 16:56.756
'Cause you're getting old.

16:56.889 --> 16:58.625
I'm 23.

16:58.758 --> 17:01.427
Well, just 'cause you're young,
doesn't mean you're not getting old.

17:01.561 --> 17:03.797
You think you're free
from the vagaries, man?

17:03.929 --> 17:05.097
Blow yourself.

17:05.231 --> 17:07.599
Have...
Have some more Sprite.

17:09.335 --> 17:15.441
You know, the last guy that
came up here, Stanley something.

17:15.575 --> 17:16.741
We had a helluva good time,

17:16.875 --> 17:19.546
but he left here thinking
I was the Devil.

17:21.579 --> 17:23.615
Um, Mr. Adams...

17:23.749 --> 17:26.051
Nah.
Don't call me that.

17:27.386 --> 17:29.588
- Okay, may I call you Micky?
- No.

17:29.721 --> 17:32.526
Anyway.
Back to the business at hand.

17:32.659 --> 17:34.894
- So there are two ways we can play this.
- Play this!

17:35.027 --> 17:37.631
- I have in my possession...
- Talk like a human.

17:37.763 --> 17:40.199
...a signed contract,
which terminates your contract,

17:40.333 --> 17:43.769
the financial terms of which I'm sure
you'll find much to your satisfaction.

17:43.903 --> 17:45.971
You're a cocky little
fucker, aren't you?

17:46.105 --> 17:48.474
Would you have some more
Spritelier Sprite?

17:49.642 --> 17:50.911
It's good.

17:53.479 --> 17:56.048
There are two ways
we could play this, Mr. Adams.

17:56.182 --> 17:57.918
You're clinging to that
phrase like a lifeboat.

17:58.050 --> 18:00.386
Now you can sign
this now, okay?

18:00.519 --> 18:02.721
Or you can sign it later,

18:02.855 --> 18:06.293
but I'm not going anywhere
till you do, okay?

18:06.425 --> 18:08.060
Follow-through, man.

18:08.193 --> 18:10.061
It's what I'm all about,
man, follow-through.

18:10.195 --> 18:13.866
Follow-through is
the street where I live.

18:15.234 --> 18:17.402
What was I saying?

18:17.537 --> 18:22.542
The contract... Sorry.
I'm a bit ADD.

18:22.674 --> 18:24.610
Fascinating. Cheers.

18:24.743 --> 18:26.245
You know what?

18:26.378 --> 18:27.913
It's Miss Nicholson's fault.

18:28.047 --> 18:29.515
Who the fuck is
Miss Nicholson?

18:29.648 --> 18:31.584
Miss Nicholson was
my fifth grade teacher.

18:31.718 --> 18:33.687
She used to peer over
my shoulder and just stare at me

18:33.819 --> 18:35.754
with these beady
little rat eyes.

18:35.888 --> 18:38.557
She'd stare at me while I was
trying to do word problems.

18:38.691 --> 18:40.526
Why the fuck am I talking
about this?

18:40.660 --> 18:43.429
I engender revelation,
Sparky.

18:43.563 --> 18:45.932
That's the street
where I live.

18:46.066 --> 18:47.365
- Mr. Adams.
- Ah!

18:47.500 --> 18:50.103
- Sorry, right. Micky!
- Ah!

18:50.236 --> 18:52.439
What do you want me
to call you then?

18:52.571 --> 18:53.772
I always liked Biff.

18:53.905 --> 18:55.907
Attention must be paid!

18:56.041 --> 18:56.775
What?

18:56.910 --> 18:58.011
"Death of a Salesman," man.

18:58.144 --> 19:00.412
Biff. Come on, Sparky.
Try to keep up.

19:00.546 --> 19:01.748
Totally.

19:01.881 --> 19:03.883
Okay, so, Biff,
I'm from Indigo Records.

19:04.017 --> 19:07.620
Yeah. As my daughter
used to say, "Duh."

19:07.752 --> 19:09.154
You have a daughter?

19:09.288 --> 19:10.856
Not according to her.

19:14.693 --> 19:17.262
Did I mention
that I'm from Indigo Records?

19:17.396 --> 19:19.064
Yeah, a lot.

19:19.199 --> 19:20.767
Cool.

19:37.784 --> 19:40.921
I take it you're aware
that your table is melting.

19:41.654 --> 19:43.655
Sure.

19:43.788 --> 19:47.093
And that the walls are...
on fire.

19:48.528 --> 19:50.029
You bet.

19:53.932 --> 19:56.568
I'm a Zamboni.
That's not what I said though.

19:56.702 --> 19:58.238
Hear voices.
You have to pay me for that.

19:58.371 --> 20:00.273
I'm seeing things.
I'm fucking hearing things!

