28:37.323 --> 28:39.592
<i>♪ Now, once again
The start, G... ♪</i>

28:40.992 --> 28:47.200
Mmm. I read the Kushner article
on you in <i>Rolling Stone.</i>

28:47.333 --> 28:49.735
It sounds like you fought
like hell to get here.

28:49.867 --> 28:53.905
Yeah, it's a real New York
bootstraps story, sure.

28:54.039 --> 28:57.343
Iovine isn't the only scrapper
out of Brooklyn, you know.

28:57.476 --> 29:00.612
My dad died when I was seven.
My mom had to go back to work.

29:00.746 --> 29:02.782
I was pretty much
on my own since then.

29:02.914 --> 29:07.451
Fuck if I wasn't getting out of that
hell hole first chance that I could.

29:12.692 --> 29:16.060
Yeah, I dug my way out, and
I won't let anything stop me.

29:16.194 --> 29:18.763
And that's what
kills me about them.

29:20.097 --> 29:21.166
Who?

29:21.299 --> 29:25.903
The... artists.

29:26.038 --> 29:28.574
Yeah,
they know pain and shit,

29:28.707 --> 29:30.876
and some of them have real
fucking talent to back it up.

29:31.009 --> 29:35.480
But what fucking kills me is
they will throw it all away

29:35.614 --> 29:40.685
over hurt feelings
and ego and shit.

29:40.819 --> 29:43.654
Axl and Slash,
Eddie V and David Lee!

29:43.788 --> 29:46.525
Yes. And who knows what
Art Garfunkel was thinking?

29:46.659 --> 29:49.094
Exactly!

29:49.228 --> 29:51.330
All right, lesson number one.

29:51.463 --> 29:53.398
Do not fall in love
with the artist.

29:53.531 --> 29:56.100
Never confuse the artist
with his art.

29:56.233 --> 29:57.435
Bob Dylan.

29:57.568 --> 30:00.638
Bob Dylan is not
"Mr. Tambourine Man."

30:00.772 --> 30:03.541
Nobody is who you think
they are, except for Vedder.

30:03.674 --> 30:05.877
Tomorrow he'll help build
another Planned Parenthood

30:06.010 --> 30:09.347
and be out there on his
longboard by three.

30:09.480 --> 30:12.084
Other than that, it's a
fucking wasteland out there.

30:12.218 --> 30:15.987
There is a hole in the
soul of rock 'n' roll.

30:16.121 --> 30:19.658
And you know what?
I think Charlie Porter could fill it, huh?

30:19.790 --> 30:22.360
That's a really big
statement, Charlie.

30:23.162 --> 30:24.096
I found this girl.

30:24.229 --> 30:25.297
Girl. What girl?

30:25.431 --> 30:27.732
Well? Look.

30:30.669 --> 30:32.972
Great eyes. Can she sing?

30:33.105 --> 30:37.309
Jesus,
look at those... eyes!

31:25.557 --> 31:27.058
You're stupid.

31:33.798 --> 31:34.532
Hey!

31:34.665 --> 31:36.134
- Hey, Big Man.
- Hi.

31:36.268 --> 31:37.736
I got your message.

31:37.868 --> 31:40.304
- Congratulations.
- Oh, thank you, thanks.

31:40.439 --> 31:42.508
- Can I come in?
- Yeah, yeah, please, come in.

31:45.644 --> 31:47.479
You must be
really excited.

31:47.612 --> 31:51.216
Oh, yeah, you kidding me?
It's unreal.

31:51.348 --> 31:53.250
Nice digs.

31:53.384 --> 31:55.086
It's so messy. I'm sorry.

31:55.220 --> 31:58.356
- Do you want a beer?
- Yeah.

32:04.128 --> 32:06.598
What's, uh,
Mr. Brand-new A&R man doing

32:06.731 --> 32:08.667
all by himself
on a Friday night?

32:10.669 --> 32:17.075
Well, he's not all by himself
now, is he? Right?

32:17.209 --> 32:19.745
No, he's not.

32:20.945 --> 32:23.048
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

32:25.750 --> 32:29.754
What did your boss say
when you mentioned me?

32:31.289 --> 32:33.759
That you have
great eyes.

32:33.893 --> 32:34.994
Yeah.

32:36.295 --> 32:38.997
And do you agree?

32:39.131 --> 32:41.033
Yeah, I do.

32:43.301 --> 32:45.103
You have an eyelash.

33:09.228 --> 33:11.663
Don't be afraid
to tell me what you want.

33:16.868 --> 33:17.903
Okay.

33:21.839 --> 33:24.676
I want a house
on Point Dume by 24...

33:26.144 --> 33:28.980
Ferrari by 25.

33:30.048 --> 33:34.886
I want Donny Rumson's job
by, like, 30.

33:36.888 --> 33:42.427
I want to master
that whisper thing he does

33:43.127 --> 33:44.596
- probably by 40.
- Yeah.

33:49.367 --> 33:52.636
I want his hair at 50.

33:52.770 --> 33:55.106
I want you to never stop
doing that.

34:02.681 --> 34:05.750
All of you is perfect,
like, this body is the one

34:05.884 --> 34:07.519
that I've been waiting for.

34:07.653 --> 34:09.286
Do you think
this body can sing?

34:09.420 --> 34:11.922
I think
this body's a symphony.

34:12.056 --> 34:14.559
Do you think
this body's a star?

34:14.693 --> 34:17.027
I think this body's
the Milky Way.

34:18.896 --> 34:20.898
Mmm.

34:21.032 --> 34:22.067
Finally.

34:52.297 --> 34:55.099
Daddy! Daddy!

34:56.268 --> 34:57.903
Daddy.

34:58.036 --> 35:00.239
Dad, come on!

35:00.371 --> 35:01.438
Are you serious?

35:01.572 --> 35:02.807
Look at me!

35:05.242 --> 35:07.578
- I thought you said he wasn't crazy.
- He's not.

35:07.713 --> 35:09.481
Dad? Get down
from there.

35:09.614 --> 35:11.115
He's just
a little bipolar.

35:11.248 --> 35:13.317
This is not amusing!

35:13.451 --> 35:14.818
With manic depressive
tendencies.

35:14.952 --> 35:16.320
- But not crazy?
- Oh, God, no!

35:16.454 --> 35:17.855
Goddamn it!
Please!

35:17.989 --> 35:19.691
Is there a specific
reason he's up there

35:19.824 --> 35:21.259
or just general non-madness?

35:21.393 --> 35:22.795
This.

35:27.199 --> 35:28.000
What the hell?

35:28.132 --> 35:29.801
It was in the Enquirer.

35:29.934 --> 35:32.436
I am but
a tarnished angel.

35:32.570 --> 35:33.706
Hey, Charlie.

35:33.838 --> 35:34.639
Hi.

35:34.773 --> 35:36.541
Um, who took this picture?

35:36.675 --> 35:40.345
Cameroon Robbins. The prick.
Charlie, why don't you come on up here?

35:40.478 --> 35:41.945
Who the fuck is
Cameroon Robbins?

35:42.079 --> 35:44.516
And why is he taking pictures
of us naked?

35:44.650 --> 35:46.017
Charlie.

35:46.150 --> 35:49.521
And uh, why don't you come
down here, Micky, huh?

35:50.422 --> 35:51.889
Okay.

35:52.023 --> 35:53.224
Okay.

35:58.028 --> 36:00.733
- Oh, shit!
- No-no-no-no!

36:02.666 --> 36:04.268
Daddy? Daddy! Well?

36:04.402 --> 36:05.536
Well, what?

36:05.670 --> 36:07.405
Well, do something!
You're the guy!

36:07.539 --> 36:08.774
Yup-yup.
Fuckin' whale.

36:08.907 --> 36:10.843
- Hurry up. Come on!
- All right.

36:20.184 --> 36:21.186
Come on, Micky.

36:21.318 --> 36:22.887
What the fuck, man?

36:24.255 --> 36:26.156
I'm tired, Charlie.

36:27.525 --> 36:29.327
Too tired today to try.

36:38.802 --> 36:41.572
He's asleep.

36:41.706 --> 36:43.541
Your clothes
are almost dry.

36:43.675 --> 36:45.410
Thanks.

36:45.543 --> 36:47.045
Who's Cameroon Robbins?

36:47.179 --> 36:49.180
He used to write for <i>Rolling
Stone</i> a million years ago

36:49.313 --> 36:52.082
before they started
putting tits on the cover.

36:52.217 --> 36:54.786
Now all he does is kind of sneak
around and stalk my father.

36:54.918 --> 36:57.355
He peeks through our windows.
He goes through our trash.

36:57.489 --> 36:59.157
He calls himself
an Adamsologist,

36:59.291 --> 37:01.927
but he's really just a
lonely old pain in the ass.

37:02.059 --> 37:04.061
Can we just get back
to the business at hand?

37:04.195 --> 37:07.399
He really needs to sign
the contract, Julia.

37:07.532 --> 37:08.834
Your father needs
to be realistic.

37:08.967 --> 37:10.401
This is
an inevitable formality.

37:10.534 --> 37:11.737
Aren't you a little young

37:11.869 --> 37:13.771
to be concerned with
inevitable formalities?

37:17.009 --> 37:19.177
The contract is not currently
in my possession, I forgot.

37:19.311 --> 37:21.746
Perhaps your dog ate it.

37:21.880 --> 37:23.882
Or perhaps
in a drug-induced stupor,

37:24.014 --> 37:25.650
I unwittingly threw it
into the ocean.

37:25.782 --> 37:27.217
Not that I have
any memory of it.

37:27.351 --> 37:29.355
Maybe you were soaring on
the wings of your better angels.

37:29.487 --> 37:32.089
I don't know what that means,
and I don't really fucking care!

37:32.224 --> 37:34.059
I got a job to do, and goddamn
it, I'm gonna do it!

37:34.193 --> 37:36.395
- Shush! You're gonna wake him up!
- Good! Somebody has to!

37:36.527 --> 37:38.262
Let me ask you something,
Mr. Charlie Porter.

37:38.396 --> 37:40.164
How would you feel if everybody
thinks you're a genius

37:40.297 --> 37:42.400
and then, whimsically, one day,
they decide that you're not.

37:42.534 --> 37:44.802
That you're uncool, over,
that you're embarrassing

37:44.936 --> 37:47.172
and that you should
maybe just go away?

37:47.304 --> 37:48.339
Or even better, die.

37:48.472 --> 37:50.041
You know what I would do?

37:51.275 --> 37:53.377
I would just sign
on the dotted line,

37:53.512 --> 37:56.181
take the money and fade
gracefully into the sunset.

37:56.313 --> 37:57.482
Fuck you.

37:57.615 --> 38:00.184
You have no idea the people
who used to hang out here.

38:00.318 --> 38:02.586
Legends. I grew up bouncing
on the knees of legends.

38:02.719 --> 38:04.488
They all took
to the hills.

38:04.623 --> 38:06.858
All that's left is me.

38:10.827 --> 38:12.230
Where's your mom?

38:14.798 --> 38:16.034
She died.

38:21.405 --> 38:22.807
My father too.

38:25.010 --> 38:28.347
Just too weird for words
isn't it, when they die?

38:31.516 --> 38:33.284
Everything stops.

38:40.559 --> 38:42.760
Oh, well,
